   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <ab type="salutationType">F2</ab>
            <p>56 West 75<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Street<lb/>
               <placeName key="49021" type="write">New
            York</placeName> 23, <placeName key="50589">N.Y.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="right">
               <date when="1947-11-02" cert="high">November 2, 1947</date>
            </p>
            <p>
               <emph n="salutation">Dear Mr. <persName key="73655" role="recipient">Schocken</persName>
               </emph>:</p>
            <p>Only yesterday did I learn from <name type="periodical" key="75026">"Aufbau"</name> that you
          have celebrated your seventieth anniversary last week. So I am unfortunately coming too
          late with my congratulations. But they are nevertheless sincere and affectionate. I have
          always looked up to you, admiring the scope of your interests and your magnificent
          readiness to translate ideas into actions. And it is a profoundly comforting thought that
          you are now carrying on with undiminished strength, in a tireless effort to spread the
          best of Jewish culture and heart. I personally owe much to what you have done and so do
          innumerable others. And I also wish to tell you on this occasion that, whenever I had the
          opportunity of talking with you, I felt deeply impressed and elated by the power and
          radiance of your personality. These rare conversations belong among my most treasured
          memories.</p>
            <p rend="center">
               <emph n="salute">Many happy returns. And all my good wishes</emph>.</p>
            <p rend="center">
               <emph n="salute">Sincerely yours</emph>,</p>
            <p rend="center">
               <persName key="7721" role="signed">Siegfried Kracauer</persName>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
